<br>
When iksar were made, the got the following as a 20% xp penaltry trade off.<br>
<br>
Regen:<br>
Innate Ac Bonus:<br>
50 swimming skill.<br>
<br>
This made for amazing monks, pretty good necros, and mediocre warriors.  Once enough warriors got to that point wearing cabalis scale crap, they began to complain.  Basically ac even with the natural ac was just not close to a ogre in full cobalt =P<br>
<br>
So then velious hit the scene, iksars got put on all of the quest armors.  Truthfully its not like they could have made seperate iksar quests in velious for sub par armor.  Velious was hardly completed on release anyways, so it was wouldnt have been valid to spent time doing that to poor iksars anyways.<br>
<br>
So once iksars were wearing PoG armor, as well as skyshrine and kael for all the classes.....<br>
<br>
What did it matter what the stats were on iksar armor?  Why not give them a slight upgrade to indicolate or spite armor for their 20% xp penalty?  They'll be wearing dwarf armor soon enough.<br>
<br>
That's my 2 cents anyways. <p><center><table COLS=2 WIDTH="400" border=1>
