<br>
When I was about 20, I looked around, and there was really only Cab Scale and Imbued Cab scale to goto from banded. Yes, you had a few old world chain items, and the Treeweave BP, but not really any version of, say, Crafted.<br>
<br>
So, Verant added the Trooper Scale Quests. About the same time they added Scaled Mystic for shaman and Dreadscale for Shadowknights. These peices had slighty less AC and slightly better stats then the softskin equilivent, in many cases.<br>
<br>
Then, just before the big &quot;Class Balance&quot; issue, they realized high level warriors where still in &quot;Crafted&quot;. So they added Legionierre Scale armor for warriors, Greenmist for Shadowknights, and... Whatever for Shamans. (You may recall that warriors had a point on there class balance- Iksar Planer Armor- It seems there isn't any)<br>
<br>
Again, these armor peices where slightly lower AC, slightly better stats/resists. <br>
<br>
Frankly, as an Iksar Warrior, I had no problem taking this, but yeah, it is a bit unfair to our Softskin breathern. We end up with similiar or the same AC, and better resists.<br>
<br>
And, IME, the drop rates on Legionierre Scale and on Indo seem about the same. It's just that there are so few Iksar to loot- IE, a typical raid may have 3-5 Softskin warriors, and maybe 1 Iksar. Therefore, it seems like the Iksar drop rate is 3-5 times more. You also get a lot more Iksar armor Rotting- Either because the Iksar already has it, or because there IS no Iksar. When a full suit of Iksar rots, and a full suit of Indo is divided agmonst 5 softskins, the impression is &quot;Wow, this Lego Scale drops ALOT&quot;.<br>
<br>
When Velious came out, well, it seems VI &quot;forgot&quot; about the armor restrictions. Now I can wear Velious Plate, and get slightly higher AC but with the same resists. Is it fair? Perhaps not. The one thing that kills me is, after Plane of Hate, and dealing with Scalemail and Chain, I was kinda used to getting defaulted drops, and now have to actually compete for em. :-)<br>
<br>
Anyhoo, brief roundup of the Iksar Armor from someone who had them added to the game about the time he needed em.<br>
<br>
Back to the Iksar Rogues- Cabilis despises rogues. It's a very regimented society, and we have no room for those who choose to act outside the society. Hence, all Iksar Bandits, Rogues, whatever, are cast out and generally join The Forsaken. If you were to have an Iksar Rogue, you could not start in Cabilis, and would most likely have to start max kos in Cab. I suppose you could add a guildmaster and maybe a few NPC's to say, Trakanons Teeth or somesuch, redo the SoNH zone so the part near TT is more newbe-friendly, etc. But it boils down to it being a lot of work to put in a race/class combo that wasn't really intended. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urustem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rustem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 5:56:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22598.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lore as I recall it.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Actually, the Iksar society according to VI has no malcontents, the usual source for rogues.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
